    "physical and chemical changes in the cellular and tissue structures, such as morphology distortion, vacuolation, and cytoplasmic basophilia 5, impeding the chemical binding between the staining dyes and biomolecules in the tissues.",
    "As a result, various staining artifacts, including poor nuclear contrast and color fading in cytoplasmicextracellular tissue staining, are introduced compared to staining of tissue samples with no processing delays, such as biopsy samples 6, 7.",
    "Even when fixation can be timely executed, a myriad of exogenous factors, including hyperthermia, sepsis, tissue hypoxia, and injuries, can destabilize tissue homeostasis and significantly increase the rate of tissue autolysis.",
    "Such affected tissue areas may contain residual water, which hampers the tissue embedding process as residual water will not be replaced by paraffin, making the tissue susceptible to degradation.",
    "Consequently, poor embedding might result in continuous tissue degradation after paraffin impregnation and low-quality staining 8."
  ]
